name: Kelly Bros.
comments: Early country and Hawaiian music duo consisting of Kelly brothers Ramon (vocals, steel guitar) and Jerry (banjo).  Their releases were credited to Masters Hawaiians, Kelly Brothers, and Kelly Family and songwriting credits as Kelly Bros. Their initial Victor recording sessions were on July 2-3, 1931. The artists were logged as Kelly Bros. but the actual releases were credited as Masters (or Masters') Hawaiians and musicians billed as Ralph Masters (i.e. Ramon) and Kelly Masters (i.e., Jerry).  This was likely because most of the sides were Hawaiian-themed. They recorded again on June 7, 1933.  The majority of these sides were again credited as Masters Hawaiians (and musicians Ralph and Kelly Masters).  The Victor label sides were credited to Kelly Brothers. There recorded again on September 18 and October 2, 1934 and these sides were released on Decca and credited to The Kelly Family or Kelly Brothers (and musicians Ramon (or Raymond) Kelly and Jerry Kelly.
